e", "united states", "filipinos"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:06:24.810Z", "title": "Filipino forum", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2022270606/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88085780/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn88085780", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/d289f0cc-52af-5cb2-9225-e3dad16365c0"], "batch": ["wa_canvasback_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1928", "description": ["Monthly Vol. 1, no. 1 (Oct. 15, 1928)- Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:10.544Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-13", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-13"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88085780/", "image_url": [], "index": 10, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [47.603229, -122.33028], "location": ["washington", "king", "pacific", "pacific northwest", "united states", "seattle"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-122.33028, 47.603229], "number": ["2024-04-18t09:34:01.476550", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88085780/1928-10-15/ed-1/", "2025-10-16t10:47:59.900000", "online resource", "18236725", "2831-6657", "sn88085780", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88085780/1963-12-10/ed-1/", "1", "243", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["catalog", "chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "filipino forum (seattle, wash.) 1928-196?", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["monthly"], "score": 71.940575, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["newspapers", "filipino american newspapers", "washington", "king", "community newspapers", "northwest, pacific", "filipino", "seattle (wash.)", "pacific northwest", "washington (state)", "seattle", "united states", "filipinos"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:27:58.371Z", "title": "Filipino forum", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn88085780/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2012203852/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["northwest fruit growers association", "washington state dairymen's association", "freeman, miller,", "washington state livestock breeders' association"], "date": "1897", "dates": ["[1897 TO 1902]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. 1, no. 1 (Apr. 8, 1897); ceased with Aug. 21, 1902. \"In the interest of the Farmers, Horticulturalists and Stockmen of Washington, Oregon, Idaho, Montana, Utah and British Columbia.\"--Publisher's statement Editor: Miller Freeman. Published in: Seattle, Wash., Aug. 26, 1897-Nov. 11, 1897; in: Seattle, Wash. and Spokane, Wash., Nov. 18, 1897-; published variously by: Ranch and Range Co., Freeman and Freeman, or Miller Freeman, Dec. 11, 1897-July 11, 1901; by: The Ranch Co., July 18, 1901- Issues for June 10, 1897- called new ser. v. 1, no. 10- and also old ser. v. 3, no. 43-, in continuation of the numbering of: The ranch.; many numbering peculiarities Nov. 11-Dec. 18, 1897; old ser. numbering dropped and new ser. designation dropped with issue for Dec. 18, 1897; issue for Mar. 16, 1899 also called v. 4, no. 52; issues for Mar. 23, 1899-Nov. 15, 1900 also called v. 15, no. 16-v. 16, no. 50; issues for Nov. 22, 1900-Aug. 21, 1902 lack numbering. Also issued in print. Mode of access: World Wide Web. Official organ of the Northwest Fruit Growers Association for Washington, Oregon, Idaho and British Columbia, May 20, 1897-Jan. 15, 1898; official organ of the Washington State Dairymen's Association and the Washington State Livestock Breeders' Association, Mar. 9, 1899- Print version record. Aug. 21, 1902 (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed August 31, 2012). Ranch (Seattle, Wash.) 2768-4229 (DLC) 2021220340 (OCoLC)701546373"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:13.555Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2012203852/", "image_url": [], "index": 11, "language": ["english"], "location": ["spokane", "\u00e9tat", "washington", "king", "pacific", "pacific northwest", "seattle", "united states", "yakima"], "number": ["2012203852", "2021220339", "online resource", "2021220340", "701546380", "2169-5164", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Issues for Oct. 7, 1897- have title: Ranch and range", "Ranch"], "partof": ["ranche and range (north yakima, wash.) 1897-1902 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 65.04338, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD S449 .R36", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "spokane", "washington (\u00e9tat)", "washington", "king", "livestock", "northwest, pacific", "yakima", "journaux", "pacific northwest", "agriculture", "seattle", "united states", "washington (state)"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:47:02.218Z", "title": "Ranche and range", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2012203852/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2007252185/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2007252185", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/e43779c9-1857-58ea-a42e-91bd076c837e"], "batch": ["wa_gilia_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["northwest fruit growers association", "washington state dairymen's association", "washington state livestock breeders' association", "freeman, miller"], "date": "1897", "description": ["Weekly Vol. 1, no. 1 (Apr. 8, 1897)-Aug. 21, 1902. \"In the interest of the Farmers, Horticulturalists and Stockmen of Washington, Oregon, Idaho, Montana, Utah and British Columbia.\"--Publisher's statement. Editor: Miller Freeman. Published in: Seattle, Wash., Aug. 26, 1897-Nov. 11, 1897; in: Seattle, Wash. and Spokane, Wash., Nov. 18, 1897-; published variously by: Ranch and Range Co., Freeman and Freeman, or Miller Freeman, Dec. 11, 1897-July 11, 1901; by: The Ranch Co., July 18, 1901- Issues for June 10, 1897- called new ser. v. 1, no. 10- and also old ser. v. 3, no. 43-, in continuation of the numbering of: The ranch.; many numbering peculiarities Nov. 11-Dec. 18, 1897; old ser. numbering dropped and new ser. designation dropped with issue for Dec. 18, 1897; issue for Mar. 16, 1899 also called v. 4, no. 52; issues for Mar. 23, 1899-Nov. 15, 1900 also called v. 15, no. 16-v. 16, no. 50; issues for Nov. 22, 1900-Aug. 21, 1902 lack numbering. Archived issues are available in digital format as part of the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Official organ of the Northwest Fruit Growers Association for Washington, Oregon, Idaho and British Columbia, May 20, 1897-Jan. 15, 1898; official organ of the Washington State Dairymen's Association and the Washington State Livestock Breeders' Association, Mar. 9, 1899- Ranch (Seattle, Wash.) 2157-8060 (DLC)sn 98047754 (OCoLC)39287946"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:10.544Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-00", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-00"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2007252185/", "image_url": [], "index": 12, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [47.6589989, -117.4250224], "location": ["spokane", "washington", "king", "pacific", "pacific northwest", "seattle", "united states", "yakima"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-117.4250224, 47.6589989], "number": ["2007252175", "2024-04-18t09:34:01.476550", "124509190", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2007252185/1897-04-08/ed-1/", "2025-12-20t10:46:57.200000", "online resource", "2007252185", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2007252185/1902-08-21/ed-1/", "1", "sn95062809", "281", "2158-2556", "sn98047754", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Issue