.loc.gov/resource/sn87093436/1948-11-01/ed-1/?sp=7"], "batch": ["wa_canvasback_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/washington/", "2/united states/washington/king/", "3/united states/washington/king/seattle/"], "contributor": ["washington state library; olympia, wa"], "date": "1948-11-01", "dates": ["1948-11-01"], "description": ["THE SCANDINAVIAN AMERICAN Evidence 0f Glacial Period 0n Hawaii Scientist Discovers STOCKHOLM Oct 15 By airmail Evidence of a glacial period on the Hawaiian Islands almost coincidental with the great climatic recession in northern Eur ope has been discovered by a Swe dish scientist Dr Olof H Selling He recently presented a thesis at the University of Stockholm deal ing with the evolution of vegetable life on Hawaii during the past ten thousand years In 1938 he was a member of an expedition to those parts headed by Prof C Skottsberg during which sample series of peat deposits were col lected These now form the base material for his thesis Dr Sellings research has thrown light on a hitherto com pletely unknown Chapter in the history of the Central Pacific The most notable result of the in vestigation is the discovery of a close similarity between the Vege tative evolution of Hawaii and that of New Zealand America and Europe This gives support to the News In Brief One Bemadotte succeeds anoth er as chief of the Swedish Boy Scouts Lennart Bernadotte only son of Prince Wilhelm has been named head of the Scout union af ter the late Count"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-04-26T11:24:26.145Z", "group": ["ndnp/wa", "washington-state-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn87093436/1948-11-01/ed-1/?sp=7", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:wa:batch_wa_canvasback_ver02:data:sn87093436:00200291463:1948110101:0119/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=340&w=229", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:wa:batch_